{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/notes/makings-mistake/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Makings of a mistake, designing the site","date":"2011-04-04T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"April 4th, 2011","date_from_now":"9 years ago","last_modified_at":"2015-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"5 years ago","path":"/notes/makings-mistake/","author":null,"excerpt":"As a designer we've all been there. When was the last time you got bored with a design and decided to just burn it and start anew?","tags":["web development","Wordpress","design"],"image":null,"toc":true,"comments":null,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":null},"id":"eaf00b53-d996-53f9-9b49-a1fab992e95d","html":"<p>As a designer we’ve all been there. When was the last time you got bored with a design and decided to just scrap it and start from scratch? Yeah, that’s what I thought.</p>\n<h2 id=\"force-feeding-a-cms\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#force-feeding-a-cms\" aria-label=\"force feeding a cms permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Force feeding a CMS</h2>\n<p>For the last decade I’ve been fighting “the loop”, squeezing my words in and out of every major web content management system, trying to tame DIV-itus, and determining what voice and creative outlets to live in. Depending on which half of my brain you asked, you’d probably get a different answer about all this madness.</p>\n<p>But you know what? I’m alright with that. I’ve always been alright with that. The first website I created that wasn’t some Geocities piece of mess was a personal project I called Faded Leaf Design.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 620px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 34.90909090909091%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Faded Leaf Design Splash Screen\"\n        title=\"Faded Leaf Design Splash Screen\"\n        data-src=\"/static/db488ee9d418fdaa4125b86aa09b0ad8/64daf/faded-leaf-design-2001.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/db488ee9d418fdaa4125b86aa09b0ad8/16841/faded-leaf-design-2001.jpg 275w,\n/static/db488ee9d418fdaa4125b86aa09b0ad8/50c97/faded-leaf-design-2001.jpg 550w,\n/static/db488ee9d418fdaa4125b86aa09b0ad8/64daf/faded-leaf-design-2001.jpg 620w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><strong>November 2001</strong>: Splash screen for Faded Leaf design website that launched a popup window containing Flash documents. Looking back at this now I can’t help but see a huge usability nightmare for visitors.</p>\n<h2 id=\"is-it-a-portfolio-or-is-it-a-blog\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#is-it-a-portfolio-or-is-it-a-blog\" aria-label=\"is it a portfolio or is it a blog permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Is it a portfolio or is it a blog?</h2>\n<p>Over time I shifted focus and came up with Made Mistakes as a concept to wrap my online portfolio in. Originally I planned to create it in <del>Macromedia</del> Adobe Flash with a simple <abbr title=\"Extensible Markup Language\">XML</abbr> backend. I quickly dropped that idea, inspired by the momentum gaining in the web standards movement around <abbr>HTML</abbr>, <abbr>CSS</abbr>, and Javascript.</p>\n<p>After creating some static HTML pages to use as a framework, I settled on replicating the look and feel into <a href=\"http://www.movabletype.org/\">Movable Type</a>. At the the time it was a popular <abbr title=\"Content Management System\">CMS</abbr> being used by other designers and made the most sense for realizing a gallery focused site with blog components.</p>\n<figure>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 620px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 32.36363636363636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Screenshots of Made Mistakes over the years\" title=\"Screenshots of Made Mistakes over the years\" data-src=\"/static/88fd00928bd8633db37283e118810cc0/64daf/made-mistakes-flash-xhtml.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/88fd00928bd8633db37283e118810cc0/16841/made-mistakes-flash-xhtml.jpg 275w,\n/static/88fd00928bd8633db37283e118810cc0/50c97/made-mistakes-flash-xhtml.jpg 550w,\n/static/88fd00928bd8633db37283e118810cc0/64daf/made-mistakes-flash-xhtml.jpg 620w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <figcaption><p>Made Mistakes started in 2001 with a Flash teaser page and later morphed into a portfolio gallery powered by Movable Type.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<h2 id=\"now-what\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#now-what\" aria-label=\"now what permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Now what?</h2>\n<p>Now I want to see what I can do to enrich my eye and skills as a designer. I’ve tired of all the constant reblogging of other’s content without attribution or added insight, and feel that I owe it to myself to do more. I suppose the only way to grow is to create often and document the process and inspirations along the way.</p>\n<figure>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 660px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 52.36363636363636%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Splash screen for an early personal website\" title=\"Splash screen for an early personal website\" data-src=\"/static/472db1412e99fcb893ae489e3d8d0070/c9129/bleedsapathy-splash-page.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/472db1412e99fcb893ae489e3d8d0070/16841/bleedsapathy-splash-page.jpg 275w,\n/static/472db1412e99fcb893ae489e3d8d0070/50c97/bleedsapathy-splash-page.jpg 550w,\n/static/472db1412e99fcb893ae489e3d8d0070/c9129/bleedsapathy-splash-page.jpg 660w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <figcaption><p>Circa 2001, my first home on the web looked like this.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 300px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 82.54545454545455%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Made Mistakes Website Sketch\" title=\"Made Mistakes Website Sketch\" data-src=\"/static/41d0da3e2c26df9c95dba398d8ee233b/85449/made-mistakes-sketch.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/41d0da3e2c26df9c95dba398d8ee233b/16841/made-mistakes-sketch.jpg 275w,\n/static/41d0da3e2c26df9c95dba398d8ee233b/85449/made-mistakes-sketch.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  <figcaption><p>Redesign sketch that never happened.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>","excerpt":"As a designer we’ve all been there. When was the last time you got bored with a design and decided to just scrap it and start from scratch…","timeToRead":2,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/makings-mistake/#force-feeding-a-cms\">Force feeding a CMS</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/makings-mistake/#is-it-a-portfolio-or-is-it-a-blog\">Is it a portfolio or is it a blog?</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/makings-mistake/#now-what\">Now what?</a></li>\n</ul>"},"comments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/notes/knowing-grids-means-breaking-grids/","title":"Knowing grids means breaking grids","categories":["notes"],"tags":["design","inspiration"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/notes/knowing-grids-means-breaking-grids.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/notes/iphone4-impressions/","title":"Impressions of iPhone 4 from a long time Palm user","categories":["notes"],"tags":["iPhone","Apple","Palm Pre","review","tech geek"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/notes/iphone4-impressions.md"}}}}